snippet.title: TRAGIC STORY OF JET AIRWAYS FOUNDER!! #informative #jetairways
snippet.description:
You won‚Äôt be able to bear the condition of Jet Airways‚Äô billionaire founder today.)

Naresh Goyal launched Jet Airways in 1993.

It became India‚Äôs number one domestic airline, and by 2005, Naresh Goyal‚Äôs net worth had crossed $1 billion.

But when new competitors like IndiGo and SpiceJet entered the market, Naresh Goyal couldn‚Äôt keep up with the changing times.

His profits declined, and he ended up with a debt of ‚Çπ8,000 crore.

In 2019, Naresh Goyal resigned from the board of his own company.

Then in 2023, he was arrested for allegedly committing a ‚Çπ540 crore bank fraud.

Today, 75-year-old Naresh Goyal has lost all hope in life.

His wife, Anita Goyal, passed away due to cancer, and he himself is also suffering from cancer.

Despite this, he has requested not to be taken to a hospital and says he would prefer to take his last breath in jail.

However, in November 2024, the court granted him permanent bail due to his poor health.
